{
  "texts": [
    "In DEPS [33], the authors argue that solely providing information about the completion of a task is often inadequate for correcting planning errors.",
    "Therefore, they propose informing the agent about the detail reasons for task failure, allowing them to more effectively revise their plans.",
    "LLM-Planner [60] introduces a grounded re-planning algorithm that dynamically updates plans generated by LLMs when encountering object mismatches and unattainable plans during task completion.",
    "Inner Monologue [61] provides three types of feedback to the agent after it takes actions: (1) whether the task is successfully Fig. 3 Comparison between the strategies of single-path and multi-path reasoning.",
    "LMZSP is the model proposed in [54] completed, (2) passive scene descriptions, and (3) active scene descriptions."
  ]
}